Zola says Chelsea almost kept <span style="color: teal;">Mason Mount</span>: &quot;I came across him when I first came over here. I was analysing the players that came on loan, <span style="color: red;">he was one of the first that I came across and I said this is one for us. Then we decided to let him go.</span>&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;Physically he needs to improve, he is getting on well. I am looking forward to seeing him play tomorrow and to see him at Stamford Bridge. I am sure he will be up for it and give more indications for us.&quot;

If Eden Hazard plays on Sunday he will become joint fifth on the most appearances at Chelsea by a overseas player (312)<br />
